    "id": "iucn-richness-2025",
    "title": "IUCN Species Richness 2025",
    "description": "Global species richness and range-weighted richness maps derived from the IUCN Red List of Threatened Species (Version 2025.1). The dataset covers five major taxonomic groups: Amphibians, Birds, Mammals, Reptiles, and Freshwater Fish. Data is available as Cloud-Optimized GeoTIFFs (COGs) for visualization and H3 Hexagonal Tilings (Resolution 8) for analysis. The H3 data is partitioned by resolution 0 cells (h0) for global scalability. Layer types include: SR (Species Richness - count of all species), THR_SR (Threatened Species Richness - count of VU, EN, CR species), and RWR (Range-Weighted Richness - sum of inverse range sizes).",
